explanation: The solution utilizes a divide-and-conquer approach. It recursively merges pairs of sorted linked lists until a single sorted linked list is obtained. The merge operation has a time complexity of O(m+n) where m and n are the lengths of the two lists being merged. The divide step has a logarithmic time complexity due to the recursive nature of the merging process.  The overall time complexity is O(N log k) where N is the total number of nodes and k is the number of linked lists. The space complexity is O(log k) due to the recursive call stack.

